The paper deals with the problem of finding heavy hitters in the turnstile streaming model, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper proposes a new deterministic linear sketch that has sublinear query time, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also gives sublinear time algorithms for related problems such as combinatorial group testing and compressed sensing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and uses techniques from sparse recovery, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also possible sub-categories.
